53CONST_EXPRESSION uint32_t s_eDataTypeSizes[DataTypeCount] =
54{
55 (uint32_t)sizeof(int8_t),
56 (uint32_t)sizeof(uint8_t),
57 (uint32_t)sizeof(int16_t),
58 (uint32_t)sizeof(uint16_t),
59 (uint32_t)sizeof(int32_t),
60 (uint32_t)sizeof(uint32_t),
61 (uint32_t)sizeof(int64_t),
62 (uint32_t)sizeof(uint64_t),
63 (uint32_t)sizeof(float),
64 (uint32_t)sizeof(double),
65 (uint32_t)0, // string, must be set to actual size by caller
66 (uint32_t)0 // binary, must be set to actual size by caller
67};
68
69inline uint32_t GetDataTypeSize(eDataType dataType)
70{
71 if (dataType >= 0 && dataType < DataTypeCount)
72 {
73 return s_eDataTypeSizes[dataType];
74 }
75 return 0;
76}
77
78#if CPP11_IS_ENABLED
79
80// dataSize can be 0 for default size, must be set for string type
81#define ADD_MAP_NO_VALIDATION(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags) (map)[std::string(name)] = { (uint32_t)offsetof(MAP_TYPE, member), (uint32_t)(dataSize == 0 ? sizeof(memberType) : dataSize), dataType, (eDataFlags)dataFlags, name }; totalSize += sizeof(memberType);
82
83// note when passing member type for arrays, it must be a reference, i.e. float&
84#define ADD_MAP(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags) \
85 ADD_MAP_NO_VALIDATION(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags); \
86 static_assert(is_same<decltype(MAP_TYPE::member), memberType>::value, "Member type is an unexpected type"); \
87 static_assert((uint32_t)(dataSize == 0 ? sizeof(memberType) : dataSize) == sizeof(memberType), "Member type is an unexpected size, sizeof(memberType)"); \
88 static_assert((uint32_t)(dataSize == 0 ? sizeof(memberType) : dataSize) == sizeof(MAP_TYPE::member), "Member type is an unexpected size, sizeof(MAP_TYPE::member)"); \
89 static_assert(s_eDataTypeSizes[dataType] == 0 || (uint32_t)(dataSize == 0 ? sizeof(memberType) : dataSize) == s_eDataTypeSizes[dataType], "Data type size does not match member size");
90#define ASSERT_SIZE(s) assert(s == sizeof(MAP_TYPE))
91
92#else
93
94#define ADD_MAP_NO_VALIDATION(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags) (map)[std::string(name)] = { (uint32_t)offsetof(MAP_TYPE, member), (uint32_t)(dataSize == 0 ? sizeof(memberType) : dataSize), dataType, (eDataFlags)dataFlags, name }; totalSize += sizeof(memberType);
95#define ADD_MAP(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags) ADD_MAP_NO_VALIDATION(map, totalSize, name, member, dataSize, dataType, memberType, dataFlags)
96#define ASSERT_SIZE(s) // not supported on VS < 2015
97
98#endif

198static void PopulateTimestampField(uint32_t id, const data_info_t** timestamps, map_name_to_info_t mappings[DID_COUNT])
199{
200 static const string timestampFields[] = { "time", "timeOfWeek", "timeOfWeekMs", "seconds" };
201 const map_name_to_info_t& offsetMap = mappings[id];
202
203 if (offsetMap.size() != 0)
204 {
205 for (size_t i = 0; i < _ARRAY_ELEMENT_COUNT(timestampFields); i++)
206 {
207 map_name_to_info_t::const_iterator timestampField = offsetMap.find(timestampFields[i]);
208 if (timestampField != offsetMap.end())
209 {
210 timestamps[id] = (const data_info_t*)&timestampField->second;
211 return;
212 }
213 }
214 }
215
216 timestamps[id] = NULLPTR; // ensure value is not garbage
217}

354static void PopulateSysParamsMappings(map_name_to_info_t mappings[DID_COUNT])
355{
356 typedef sys_params_t MAP_TYPE;
357 map_name_to_info_t& m = mappings[DID_SYS_PARAMS];

2623
2624bool cISDataMappings::StringToVariable(const char* stringBuffer, int stringLength, const uint8_t* dataBuffer, eDataType dataType, uint32_t dataSize, int radix, bool json)
2625{
2626 switch (dataType)
2627 {
2628 case DataTypeInt8:
2629 *(int8_t*)dataBuffer = (int8_t)strtol(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2630 break;
2631
2632 case DataTypeUInt8:
2633 *(uint8_t*)dataBuffer = (uint8_t)strtoul(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2634 break;
2635
2636 case DataTypeInt16:
2637 *(int16_t*)dataBuffer = (int16_t)strtol(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2638 break;
2639
2640 case DataTypeUInt16:
2641 *(uint16_t*)dataBuffer = (uint16_t)strtoul(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2642 break;
2643
2644 case DataTypeInt32:
2645 *(int32_t*)dataBuffer = (int32_t)strtol(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2646 break;
2647
2648 case DataTypeUInt32:
2649 *(uint32_t*)dataBuffer = (uint32_t)strtoul(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2650 break;
2651
2652 case DataTypeInt64:
2653 *(int64_t*)dataBuffer = (int64_t)strtoll(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2654 break;
2655
2656 case DataTypeUInt64:
2657 *(uint64_t*)dataBuffer = (uint64_t)strtoull(stringBuffer, NULL, radix);
2658 break;
2659
2660 case DataTypeFloat:
2661 *(float*)dataBuffer = strtof(stringBuffer, NULL);
2662 break;
2663
2664 case DataTypeDouble:
2665 *(double*)dataBuffer = strtod(stringBuffer, NULL);
2666 break;
2667
2668 case DataTypeString:
2669 {
2670 string s2(stringBuffer);
2671 if (json)
2672 {
2673 char c;
2674 bool escaped = false;
2675 for (size_t i = 0; i < s2.size(); i++)
2676 {
2677 c = s2[i];
2678 if (c == '\\')
2679 {
2680 if (!escaped)
2681 {
2682 escaped = true;
2683 s2.erase(i);
2684 continue;
2685 }
2686 }
2687 escaped = false;
2688 }
2689 s2 = stringBuffer;
2690 }
2691 else
2692 {
2693 s2.erase(std::remove(s2.begin(), s2.end(), '"'), s2.end());
2694 }
2695 // ensure string fits with null terminator
2696 s2.resize(dataSize - 1);
2697 memcpy((void*)dataBuffer, s2.data(), s2.length());
2698 memset((uint8_t*)dataBuffer + s2.length(), 0, dataSize - s2.length());
2699 } break;
2700
2701 case DataTypeBinary:
2702 {
2703 // convert hex data back to binary
2704 size_t len = _MIN(1020, stringLength);
2705 len -= (len % 2);
2706 uint8_t* ptr2 = (uint8_t*)dataBuffer;
2707 for (size_t i = 0; i != len; i += 2)
2708 {
2709 *ptr2 = (getHexValue(stringBuffer[i + 1]) << 4) | getHexValue(stringBuffer[i + 2]);
2710 }
2711 } break;
2712
2713 default:
2714 return false;
2715 }
2716
2717 return true;
2718}

2721bool cISDataMappings::DataToString(const data_info_t& info, const p_data_hdr_t* hdr, const uint8_t* datasetBuffer, data_mapping_string_t stringBuffer, bool json)
2722{
2723 const uint8_t* ptr;
2724 if (!CanGetFieldData(info, hdr, datasetBuffer, ptr))
2725 {
2726 // pick a default string
2727 if (info.dataType == DataTypeString)
2728 {
2729 stringBuffer[0] = '"';
2730 stringBuffer[1] = '"';
2731 stringBuffer[2] = '\0';
2732 }
2733 else if (info.dataType == DataTypeBinary)
2734 {
2735 if (json)
2736 {
2737 stringBuffer[0] = '"';
2738 stringBuffer[1] = '"';
2739 stringBuffer[2] = '\0';
2740 }
2741 else
2742 {
2743 stringBuffer[0] = '\0';
2744 }
2745 }
2746 else
2747 {
2748 stringBuffer[0] = '0';
2749 stringBuffer[1] = '\0';
2750 }
2751 return false;
2752 }
2753
2754 return VariableToString(info.dataType, info.dataFlags, ptr, datasetBuffer, info.dataSize, stringBuffer, json);
2755}

2757
2758bool cISDataMappings::VariableToString(eDataType dataType, eDataFlags dataFlags, const uint8_t* ptr, const uint8_t* dataBuffer, uint32_t dataSize, data_mapping_string_t stringBuffer, bool json)
2759{
2760 switch (dataType)
2761 {
2762 case DataTypeInt8:
2763 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2764 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%02X", *(int8_t*)ptr);
2765 else
2766 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%d", (int)*(int8_t*)ptr);
2767 break;
2768
2769 case DataTypeUInt8:
2770 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2771 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%02X", *(uint8_t*)ptr);
2772 else
2773 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%u", (unsigned int)*(uint8_t*)ptr);
2774 break;
2775
2776 case DataTypeInt16:
2777 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2778 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%04X", *(int16_t*)ptr);
2779 else
2780 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%d", (int)*(int16_t*)ptr);
2781 break;
2782
2783 case DataTypeUInt16:
2784 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2785 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%04X", *(uint16_t*)ptr);
2786 else
2787 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%u", (unsigned int)*(uint16_t*)ptr);
2788 break;
2789
2790 case DataTypeInt32:
2791 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2792 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%08X", *(int32_t*)ptr);
2793 else
2794 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%d", (int)*(int32_t*)ptr);
2795 break;
2796
2797 case DataTypeUInt32:
2798 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2799 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%08X", *(uint32_t*)ptr);
2800 else
2801 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%u", (unsigned int)*(uint32_t*)ptr);
2802 break;
2803
2804 case DataTypeInt64:
2805 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2806 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%016llX", (long long)*(uint64_t*)ptr);
2807 else
2808 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%lld", (long long)*(int64_t*)ptr);
2809 break;
2810
2811 case DataTypeUInt64:
2812 if (dataFlags == DataFlagsDisplayHex)
2813 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "0x%016llX", (unsigned long long)*(uint64_t*)ptr);
2814 else
2815 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%llu", (unsigned long long)*(uint64_t*)ptr);
2816 break;
2817
2818 case DataTypeFloat:
2819 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%.9g", *(float*)ptr);
2820 break;
2821
2822 case DataTypeDouble:
2823 SNPRINTF(stringBuffer, IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, "%.17g", *(double*)ptr);
2824 break;
2825
2826 case DataTypeString:
2827 {
2828 stringBuffer[0] = '"';
2829 int tempIndex = 1;
2830 char* bufPtr2 = (char*)(ptr);
2831 char* bufPtrEnd = bufPtr2 + _MIN(IS_DATA_MAPPING_MAX_STRING_LENGTH, dataSize) - 3;
2832 for (; bufPtr2 < bufPtrEnd && *bufPtr2 != '\0'; bufPtr2++)
2833 {
2834 if (json)
2835 {
2836 if (IS_JSON_ESCAPE_CHAR(*bufPtr2))
2837 {
2838 if (bufPtr2 < bufPtrEnd - 1)
2839 {
2840 stringBuffer[tempIndex++] = '\\';
2841 }
2842 else
2843 {
2844 break;
2845 }
2846 }
2847 }
2848 stringBuffer[tempIndex++] = *bufPtr2;
2849 }
2850 stringBuffer[tempIndex++] = '"';
2851 stringBuffer[tempIndex] = '\0';
2852 } break;
2853
2854 case DataTypeBinary:
2855 {
2856 size_t hexIndex = 1;
2857 if (json)
2858 {
2859 stringBuffer[0] = '"';
2860 }
2861 // convert to hex
2862 const unsigned char* hexTable = getHexLookupTable();
2863 for (size_t i = 0; i < dataSize; i++)
2864 {
2865 stringBuffer[hexIndex++] = hexTable[0x0F & (dataBuffer[i] >> 4)];
2866 stringBuffer[hexIndex++] = hexTable[0x0F & dataBuffer[i]];
2867 }
2868 if (json)
2869 {
2870 stringBuffer[hexIndex++] = '"';
2871 }
2872 stringBuffer[hexIndex] = '\0';
2873 } break;
2874
2875 default:
2876 stringBuffer[0] = '\0';
2877 return false;
2878 }
2879 return true;
2880}
2881
2882double cISDataMappings::GetTimestamp(const p_data_hdr_t* hdr, const uint8_t* buf)
2883{
2884 if (hdr == NULL || buf == NULL || hdr->id == 0 || hdr->id >= DID_COUNT || hdr->size == 0)
2885 {
2886 return 0.0;
2887 }
2888
2889 // raw data types with observation use a custom timestamp function
2890 if (hdr->id == DID_GPS1_RAW || hdr->id == DID_GPS2_RAW || hdr->id == DID_GPS_BASE_RAW)
2891 {
2892 gps_raw_t* raw = (gps_raw_t*)buf;
2893 if (raw->dataType == eRawDataType::raw_data_type_observation && raw->obsCount>0)
2894 {
2895 const obsd_t& obs = raw->data.obs[0];
2896 return obs.time.sec + (double)obs.time.time;
2897 }
2898 return 0.0;
2899 }
2900
2901#if PLATFORM_IS_EMBEDDED
2902
2903 if (s_map == NULLPTR)
2904 {
2905 s_map = new cISDataMappings();
2906 }
2907
2908#endif
2909
2910 const data_info_t* timeStampField =
2911
2912#if PLATFORM_IS_EMBEDDED
2913
2914 s_map->m_timestampFields[hdr->id];
2915
2916#else
2917
2918 s_map.m_timestampFields[hdr->id];
2919
2920#endif
2921
2922 if (timeStampField != NULLPTR)
2923 {
2924 const uint8_t* ptr;
2925 if (CanGetFieldData(*timeStampField, hdr, (uint8_t*)buf, ptr))
2926 {
2927 if (timeStampField->dataType == DataTypeDouble)
2928 {
2929 // field is seconds, use as is
2930 return *(double*)ptr;
2931 }
2932 else if (timeStampField->dataType == DataTypeUInt32)
2933 {
2934 // field is milliseconds, convert to seconds
2935 return 0.001 * (*(uint32_t*)ptr);
2936 }
2937 }
2938 }
2939 return 0.0;
2940}
2941
2942bool cISDataMappings::CanGetFieldData(const data_info_t& info, const p_data_hdr_t* hdr, const uint8_t* buf, const uint8_t*& ptr)
2943{
2944 if (buf == NULL)
2945 {
2946 return false;
2947 }
2948 else if (hdr == NULL)
2949 {
2950 // assume buf is large enough for the full data structure
2951 ptr = buf + info.dataOffset;
2952 return true;
2953 }
2954 int32_t fullSize = (hdr->size == 0 ? GetSize(hdr->id) : hdr->size);
2955 int32_t offset = (int32_t)info.dataOffset - (int32_t)hdr->offset;
2956 if (offset >= 0 && offset <= fullSize - (int32_t)info.dataSize)
2957 {
2958 ptr = (buf + offset);
2959 return true;
2960 }
2961 ptr = NULL;
2962 return false;
2963}
